"when sperm and egg come together there is nothing else needed to determine whether it will grow to be a human or not"Are you sure you're not forgetting something? I think you'll find that the result of mixing those two in a dish will result in a smelly mess, and not a human.And if you're taking the presence of a uterus and functioning placenta, blood supply protective host immune system and the rest for granted, then why bother with niceties like mixing the sperm and ovum? Why not say that the mere presence of sperm and ovum is enough for the die to be cast?